theorem dense_left_of_dense_prod
    {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y] [Nonempty Y]
    {A : Set X} {B : Set Y} :
    Dense (A ×ˢ B) → Dense A := by
  intro hDenseProd
  -- The closure of the product is the whole space.
  have hProdUniv :
      (closure (A ×ˢ B) : Set (X × Y)) = (Set.univ : Set (X × Y)) := by
    simpa using hDenseProd.closure_eq
  -- Express this closure as the product of the individual closures.
  have hProdEq :
      (closure (A ×ˢ B) : Set (X × Y)) =
        closure (A : Set X) ×ˢ closure (B : Set Y) := by
    simpa using closure_prod_eq (s := A) (t := B)
  -- Show that the closure of `A` is the whole space.
  have hClosureA_univ : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    -- `closure A ⊆ univ` holds trivially.
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro _ _; trivial
    · -- For the reverse inclusion, fix any `x : X`.
      intro x _
      classical
      -- Choose an arbitrary `y : Y`.
      let y : Y := Classical.arbitrary Y
      -- The point `(x, y)` belongs to `univ`, hence to the product of closures.
      have hxy :
          ((x, y) : X × Y) ∈ closure (A : Set X) ×ˢ closure (B : Set Y) := by
        have : ((x, y) : X × Y) ∈ (Set.univ : Set (X × Y)) := by
          trivial
        simpa [hProdUniv, hProdEq] using this
      -- Extract the `X`–component.
      exact (Set.mem_prod.1 hxy).1
  -- Translate the closure equality into density.
  exact (dense_iff_closure_eq (s := A)).2 hClosureA_univ

theorem closure_interior_idempotent {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (interior A)) = closure (interior A) := by
  -- The interior of an open set is itself.
  have h : interior (interior A) = interior A := by
    simpa using (isOpen_interior (A := A)).interior_eq
  simpa [h]
